@node MAIN "rawkey_plugin: Introduction"


    @{b}rawkey plugin@{ub}

        by @{b}Fabio Rotondo@{ub} <fsoft@intercom.it>



    @{b}rawkey plugin@{ub} is a PLUGIN that offers a
    simple way to get keyboard events from the user even
    if he is not accessing a GUI gadget (the window *MUST*
    be active anyway).

    This plugin is a _passive_ plugin, ie. it not renders
    anything on the window. It can handle events from these
    keys:

        Cursors Keys,
        Ctrl key,
        Shift keys (it *do* distinguish between the two keys)
        Alt keys   (it *do* distinguish between the two keys)
        Amiga keys (it *do* distinguish between the two keys)
        Help key
        Function keys


    ------------------------------------------------------------

    @{"  " link rawkey_USAGE}  Usage

    @{"  " link rawkey_HISTORY}  History

@endnode

@node rawkey_USAGE "rawkey_plugin: Usage"

    @{b}rawkey plugin@{ub}

    This plugin acts as a "filter" between the window and the user events.
    You can react to user actions by setting the right answer event to
    user inputs.

    As I mentioned above, you can monitor some keys:

        Cursors Keys,
        Ctrl key,
        Shift keys (it *do* distinguish between the two keys)
        Alt keys   (it *do* distinguish between the two keys)
        Amiga keys (it *do* distinguish between the two keys)
        Help key
        Function keys

    To set a relationship between a key and an action you just have
    to define a PROC that will handle that specific event, using
    the setattrs() method.

    For example, to set an event for the cursor-up key, just do:

        [PLA_KEY_UP, {proc_up}]

    Please, note that the taglist should be NIL terminated.

    The PROC proc_up will do something for the cursor-up key, for
    example, I use this to move up/down the current selection on a 
    ListView gadget.

    The PROC proc_up can will receive a parameter (that defaults to NIL)
    that can be set by the programmer using the tag: PLA_KEY_USERDATA.

    @{b}rawkey plugin@{ub} has these publically accessible methods:

        @{b}PROC init() OF rawkey@{ub}

            This method is most likely the one that you would call when
            @{b}NEW@{ub}'ing the object; but it is safe to call at other
            times to reset all procs to NIL.

        @{b}PROC setattrs(@{FG shine}tags@{FG text}) OF rawkey@{ub}

            This method sets the relationships between a key and a proc.

            @{FG shine} tags @{FG text} is a standard taglist, that should
            be NIL terminated. Here are all valid tags:


            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_UP     @{FG text} - Cursor-up key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_DOWN   @{FG text} - Cursor-down key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_RIGHT  @{FG text} - Cursor-right key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_LEFT   @{FG text} - Cursor-left key

            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_CONTROL@{FG text} - CTRL key

            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_LSHIFT @{FG text} - Left shift key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_RSHIFT @{FG text} - Right shift key

            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_LALT   @{FG text} - Left alt key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_RALT   @{FG text} - Right alt key

            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_LAMIGA @{FG text} - Left Amiga key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_RAMIGA @{FG text} - Right Amiga key

            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_HELP   @{FG text} - Help key

            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F1     @{FG text} - F1 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F2     @{FG text} - F2 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F3     @{FG text} - F3 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F4     @{FG text} - F4 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F5     @{FG text} - F5 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F6     @{FG text} - F6 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F7     @{FG text} - F7 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F8     @{FG text} - F8 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F9     @{FG text} - F9 key
            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_F10    @{FG text} - F10 key

            @{FG shine}PLA_KEY_USERDATA@{FG text} - Optional argument passed to function




    See the example source code, @{b}rawkey_demo.e@{ub}, for some actual examples
    of this plugin in use.

@endnode

